This paper discusses hardware accelerations of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation of binary neural networks and stochastic computing based neural networks, which are related to computer architecture and digital circuits. Therefore, cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.ET (Embedded Systems) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses energy consumption, which is related to control systems and optimization. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the accuracy and universal applicability of these techniques, which is related to error analysis and statistics. Therefore, cs.EM (Emerging Technologies) is a possible sub-category.
